This page provides a list of the FHIR artifacts defined as part of this implementation guide.


Structures: Resource Profiles {% capture grouping_desc %}These define constraints on FHIR resources for systems conforming to this implementation guide.{% endcapture %}
    {{ grouping_desc | markdownify}}





               Antigen Supporting Data

            {% capture desc %}A resource to store supporting data for antigens including target disease, vaccine groups, immunity criteria, contraindications, and vaccination series.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Schedule Supporting Data

            {% capture desc %}This resource consolidates various mapping and conflict information related to vaccine scheduling to support decision-making processes.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Vaccination Patient

            {% capture desc %}A profile that extends the base FHIR Patient resource to include detailed vaccination-related information.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Vaccine

            {% capture desc %}Simple vaccine to easily obtain needed information for forecasting{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}





Structures: Extension Definitions {% capture grouping_desc %}These define constraints on FHIR data types for systems conforming to this implementation guide.{% endcapture %}
    {{ grouping_desc | markdownify}}





               AssessmentDate

            {% capture desc %}The date on which the vaccination assessment was made.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}





Terminology: Value Sets {% capture grouping_desc %}These define sets of codes used by systems conforming to this implementation guide.{% endcapture %}
    {{ grouping_desc | markdownify}}





               Vaccine Gender

            {% capture desc %}A value set that groups detailed genders from SNOMED CT and LOINC into broader categories (male, female, transgender, other) for use in vaccine predictions.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}





